# reinguard bridge (Adapter layer)

This file is an **adapter**: it points at the Semantics layer (`.reinguard/`)
and Substrate (`rgd`). Do not duplicate body text from `.reinguard/` here.

## Language

Use **English for everything except replies in the Cursor chat panel to the user**. In practice that means: commit messages, PR titles and bodies, GitHub review comments and thread dispositions, code and tests (identifiers, comments, docstrings you add), command output you author for logs or docs, and any other durable or third-party-facing text — **English only**. The **chat transcript** (what you write back to the user in this Cursor conversation) may follow the user’s language preference when it differs.

## Entry points

- **Substrate config**: [.reinguard/reinguard.yaml](../../.reinguard/reinguard.yaml) — `schema_version`, `default_branch`, `providers` (ADR-0008, ADR-0009).
- **Label SSOT**: [.reinguard/labels.yaml](../../.reinguard/labels.yaml) — GitHub label categories and `commit_prefix` (ADR-0008).
- **Knowledge catalog**: [.reinguard/knowledge/manifest.json](../../.reinguard/knowledge/manifest.json) — `entries[]` with `id`, `path`, `description`, `triggers`, `when` (ADR-0010).
- **Policy catalog** (normative, not in knowledge manifest): [.reinguard/policy/catalog.yaml](../../.reinguard/policy/catalog.yaml) — `entries[]` with `id`, `path`, `description`; bodies live under [.reinguard/policy/](../../.reinguard/policy/).
- **Control catalog** (human-maintained index; not read by validate): [.reinguard/control/catalog.yaml](../../.reinguard/control/catalog.yaml) — `entries[]` with `id`, `path`, `type`, `description`. **Rule YAML** under [.reinguard/control/states/](../../.reinguard/control/states/), [routes/](../../.reinguard/control/routes/), [guards/](../../.reinguard/control/guards/) — consumed by `config.Load` / `rgd config validate`.
- **Procedures** (agent action cards; ADR-0011, ADR-0013): [.reinguard/procedure/](../../.reinguard/procedure/) — Cursor: [`rgd-next.md`](../commands/rgd-next.md), [`cursor-plan.md`](../commands/cursor-plan.md).

