## Workflow

Follow [.reinguard/policy/workflow--pr-discipline.md](../../.reinguard/policy/workflow--pr-discipline.md). Which procedures apply to which FSM `state_id` / `route_id` is defined in each procedure’s YAML front matter (`applies_to`) and in [ADR-0013 § 4](../../docs/adr/0013-fsm-workflow-states-and-adapter-mapping.md) (*Adapter mapping*). After Sense and Route, `rgd-next` applies [`.reinguard/procedure/next-orchestration.md`](../../.reinguard/procedure/next-orchestration.md) (single full-path proposal, one approval gate, then Execute). Adapter flow: [`rgd-next.md`](../commands/rgd-next.md) § **Propose** then § **Execute**.

### rgd-next Execute — Cursor chat transcript (Adapter)

Normative contract: [`.reinguard/procedure/next-orchestration.md`](../../.reinguard/procedure/next-orchestration.md) § Post-approval execution contract, § Loop semantics, § Output. Command surface: [`.cursor/commands/rgd-next.md`](../commands/rgd-next.md) § Execute. Do not restate Semantics here; this subsection only constrains **what may appear in the Cursor chat panel** after the user has given the **single Execute approval**.

After that approval, the agent’s **only** permitted **chat** output is the **final report**: Per-unit Definition of Done satisfied with evidence, or an **allowed stop** with evidence (see `next-orchestration.md` § Post-approval execution contract and § Output). Iteration summaries, guard checks, and procedure progress are **agent-internal** (tool logs, internal notes) and **do not** appear in chat. The agent still follows § Loop semantics and mapped procedures; lack of per-iteration chat is not an excuse to skip Sense → Route → Act → Refresh.

Cursor may persist an Adapter-local resume artifact under
`.reinguard/local/adapter/rgd-next/` (gitignored) via
`.reinguard/scripts/adapter-rgd-next-resume.sh` (ADR-0015): `start`
before the approval gate (`pending_approval`), then `approve` after the user
approves Execute. That artifact exists only to decide **resume vs fresh run**
on a later chat turn; it is **not** substrate state and must not be surfaced
through `rgd context build`, FSM rules, guards, or `gates.<id>.*`.

### GitHub and git observation

- **Primary:** `rgd observe` and `rgd context build` — structured observation and FSM-facing signals (see [`docs/cli.md`](../../docs/cli.md), ADR-0006, ADR-0009).
- **Supplementary:** `gh` and `git` for read-only GitHub or Git facts when you need ad-hoc checks or `rgd` is not available; GitHub tool auth uses `gh` per ADR-0006. Prefer stable behavior in tests and CI over one-off scripts.

### Agent procedure reference

Procedure **bodies** live under [`.reinguard/procedure/`](../../.reinguard/procedure/) (SSOT). **Cursor entries:** [`rgd-next.md`](../commands/rgd-next.md) — `rgd context build`, Route, **Propose** (once), then **Execute** with `next-orchestration.md`; [`cursor-plan.md`](../commands/cursor-plan.md) — `AskQuestion` / `CreatePlan` only (`gh issue create` appears as plan todos when issue-first). **After `cursor-plan` acceptance, execution must use `rgd-next` loop semantics** (`next-orchestration.md` § Loop semantics) — `cursor-plan` does not define execution; it produces the plan that `rgd-next` Execute consumes.

